<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<!--
FastDDS profile: disable the shared-memory transport, use UDPv4 only.

WHY (hardware-root-caused 2026-07-17, R1 Lite onboard):
FastDDS delivers same-host data by writing into the READER's shared-memory
segment under /dev/shm. The Galaxea stack runs as `r1lite` (uid 1000); a
container running as root creates its reader segments owned by root, so the
vendor's publishers cannot write into them. Discovery (UDP multicast) still
works, so `ros2 topic list` shows all 67 /hdas topics while `ros2 topic hz`
reports NOTHING — the "topics visible, zero messages" trap. Sharing /dev/shm
into the container does NOT fix this; the block is uid ownership, not the mount.

Two fixes work, both hardware-verified at 200 Hz on /hdas/feedback_arm_left:
  1. run the container as the vendor's uid (see scripts/galaxea compose `user:`)
     — keeps SHM zero-copy, best for large payloads (pointclouds).
  2. this profile — root-safe and uid-agnostic, at the cost of SHM. Fine for
     the R1 Lite's traffic (200 Hz JointStates + compressed 15 Hz images) and
     immune to whatever uid a customer's vendor stack happens to use.

Use: export FASTRTPS_DEFAULT_PROFILES_FILE=/app/scripts/r1lite_test/fastdds_udp_only.xml
-->
<profiles xmlns="http://www.eprosima.com/XMLSchemas/fastRTPS_Profiles">
    <transport_descriptors>
        <transport_descriptor>
            <transport_id>udp_only_transport</transport_id>
            <type>UDPv4</type>
        </transport_descriptor>
    </transport_descriptors>

    <participant profile_name="udp_only_participant" is_default_profile="true">
        <rtps>
            <userTransports>
                <transport_id>udp_only_transport</transport_id>
            </userTransports>
            <!-- false: do not add the default SHM+UDP builtin transports back -->
            <useBuiltinTransports>false</useBuiltinTransports>
        </rtps>
    </participant>
</profiles>
